,\"text\":\"**Examining test coverage concerns**\\n\\nI'm thinking that the task involves test coverage for active dynamic access, especially since the user points out that the source context relates to an active class. They might only expect a test file. I should inspect build results to see if previous native tests passed without TreeMultimap. If I add a native test, I could fail due to missing metadata. So, I need to ensure TreeMultimap metadata is included and check for serialization.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating TreeMultimap tests**\\n\\nI'm realizing there are no existing tests for TreeMultimap, so it might not be needed since native Java serialization can handle unregistered types. However, the new Graal setup seems to require registration for serializables. I should check if previous serialization tests passed, as they only required metadata for Hash* classes, and it looks like NaturalOrdering wasn't reached. Using null comparators isn’t possible directly, but I could use custom comparators from the test file. I'll need to investigate further to confirm.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_gVsEvCaaxnBStSmosBXgkFbG|fc_01099a3bf2c1be6d0169f54f222ec481a2b442c2a8b8caedaf", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/main/extracted/com/google/common/collect/NaturalOrdering.java"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"/home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/main/extracted/com/google/common/collect/NaturalOrdering.java\"}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ydiphLxZN90Bk7hgNYlKQpOi|fc_01099a3bf2c1be6d0169f54f222ee481a2bd1709db5984b0a0", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.google.